    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const items = $input.all();\nconst services = {};\nfor (const it of items) {\n  if (it.json && it.json.service) services[it.json.service] = it.json.status;\n}\nconst statuses = Object.values(services);\nconst overall = statuses.length > 0 && statuses.every(s => s === 'up') ? 'healthy' : 'degraded';\nconst down = Object.keys(services).filter(k => services[k] !== 'up');\nreturn [{ json: { checkedAt: new Date().toISOString(), overall, services, down } }];"
      },
      "id": "node-report",
      "name": "Health Report",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [-400, 208],
      "notes": "Aggregates all four checks into one report: overall=healthy only if every dependency is up; otherwise degraded with the list of down services."
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-overview",
      "name": "Sticky: Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-1260, -200],
      "parameters": {
        "width": 1000,
        "height": 180,
        "color": 5,
        "content": "## KB Ops — Health Checks\n\n**Purpose:** On-demand dependency probe for the KB stack. Run before a big ingestion or when debugging outages.\n\n**Flow:** `Manual -> [ OpenAI | Pinecone | Drive | Perplexity ] checks (parallel) -> Up/Down per service -> Health Report`.\n\n**Resilience:** each probe uses `continue-on-error`, so one dead dependency never aborts the others. Report aggregates to overall `healthy` / `degraded` with per-service status."
      }
    }
  ],
